            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the beef has browned, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>chopped chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>half</strong> your <strong>soy sauce </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) to the pan</p><p>Cook for a further 2 min or until fragrant, then add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> with your <strong>red chilli relish</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cook for 2 min or until the beef is sticky and cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>Thai-style sticky chilli beef</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1673867331103-x200.jpg",
